Comment_glosser: According to the contributor, Malto only remains two traditional Dravidian numerals 1 to 2 used adjectively, they adopt Indo-Aryan numeral system for general counting now.
'ɖeɖ’ is borrowed from Indo-Aryan which means ‘one and a  half (1½)’
'aɽaːy’ is borrowed Indo-Aryan which means ‘two and a  half (2½)’
